id: pm-n28v
title: "CI: cache .agents/pm/search/lancedb + sentry release cache"
description: Tests and reindex flows generate a lancedb cache (~50MB) and sentry sourcemap upload caches. Caching them between runs avoids cold rebuild every time. Use actions/cache@v5 with restore-keys fallback. Skip cache invalidation when only docs change.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: cache,ci,performance,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-16T22:07:59.834Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T11:31:45.578Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: lancedb cache restored on warm runs; sentry release cache restored when present; cache keys deterministic; no test runs against stale cache.
parent: pm-tzwy
resolution: CI/nightly/release/auto-release now restore LanceDB and Sentry CLI caches with deterministic keys and restore-keys.
expected_result: Warm workflow executions reuse vector index and Sentry upload caches to reduce repeated setup overhead without stale-cache regressions.
actual_result: "All targeted workflows include pinned observability cache steps, workflow contracts lock the snippets, and linked/full gates plus dogfood/observability checks are green."
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-17T11:17:24.078Z",codex-agent,"Implementation progress 2026-05-17: added dedicated observability cache restore step to CI/nightly/release/auto-release workflows using pinned actions/cache@v5 for .agents/pm/search/lancedb and ~/.cache/sentry-cli with deterministic hash keys + restore-keys (node-specific where applicable). Updated tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts to pin new cache step names/paths/keys across all four workflows. Focused regression check passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts (4 tests)."
  "2026-05-17T11:24:40.483Z",codex-agent,"UX polish 2026-05-17: reduced gate log noise/token bloat by switching npm pack dry-run invocation in scripts/release/run-gates.mjs to --silent. This keeps packaging verification intact but avoids massive tarball file listing output during local and CI troubleshooting loops."
  "2026-05-17T11:31:17.857Z",codex-agent,"Verification evidence 2026-05-17: pm test pm-n28v --run --progress passed all 4 linked checks (run_id test-local-mp9p1ujz-zjy2f5), including dogfood temp-project run (54 commands), full run-gates required mode, focused workflow contract test, and check-secrets. Standalone sentry/telemetry gate also passed with critical=0 high=0 total=0, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.11, missing_error_code_rows=0. pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift now reports resolution status OK (0 missing fields) with only pre-existing history drift warnings on 13 legacy items; pm health --check-only --no-refresh shows telemetry queue healthy (queue_entries=2, invalid_rows=0, draining=true, latest successful flush timestamp present)."
